Question: Do you think strict gun control laws would reduce violent crimes?
Answer:
According to me strict gun control laws would reduce the risks of violent crimes because I already heard that most of these crimes happened in a domestic context. A lot of violent crimes thus happen because a person in the family makes use of the gun against his own blood, and not against some people threatening the family. So even if a lot of criminals would still find a way to get guns with strict laws, it would at least prevent law-abiding citizens from being tempting to make use of these weapons just because they own one.